  "text": "Much work is limited by challenges out of the scope of RL, such as the performance of density models [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] or predictive models [Nachum et al., 2018; [CITATION_3] , or the difficulty to approximate mutual information between two continuous random variables [CITATION_4] . These limitations are beyond the scope of this article and we focus here only on challenges related to RL. Despite the heterogeneity of work on intrinsic motivation in RL and the specific limitations of each method, we select and present in this section five major issues and challenges related to these approaches.",
